{"title_page": "Defending Jacob (miniseries)", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| name                     = Defending Jacob\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Crime drama]]\n| creator                  = [[Mark Bomback]]\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Defending Jacob]]''|[[William Landay]]}}\n| writer                   = Mark Bomback\n| director                 = [[Morten Tyldum]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]]\n* [[Michelle Dockery]]\n* [[Jaeden Martell]]\n* [[Cherry Jones]]\n* [[Pablo Schreiber]]\n* [[Betty Gabriel]]\n* [[Sakina Jaffrey]]\n}}\n| composer                 = [[Atli Orvarsson]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = 3\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Mark Bomback\n* Chris Evans\n* Morten Tyldum\n* Rosalie Swedlin\n* Adam Shulman\n}}\n| producer                 = \n| cinematography           = [[Jonathan Freeman (cinematographer)|Jonathan Freeman]]\n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Mimir Films\n* Mark Bomback Productions\n* {{nowrap|[[Paramount Television Studios]]}}\n* [[Anonymous Content]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| network                  = [[Apple TV+]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = \n}}\n'''''Defending Jacob''''' is an American [[crime drama]] [[web television]] miniseries, based on the [[Defending Jacob|novel of the same name]] by [[William Landay]], produced by [[Apple TV+]]. The series was created and written by [[Mark Bomback]] and directed by [[Morten Tyldum]]. It stars [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], [[Michelle Dockery]], [[Jaeden Martell]], [[Cherry Jones]], [[Pablo Schreiber]], [[Betty Gabriel]], [[Sakina Jaffrey]] and Debbe Lewis. It premiered on April 24, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/apple-tv-plus-amazing-stories-premiere-date-1203472094/ |last=Turchiano |first=Danielle |title=Apple TV Plus Announces Premiere Dates for Steven Spielberg\u2019s \u2018Amazing Stories,\u2019 \u2018Defending Jacob,\u2019 More |date=January 19, 2020 |accessdate=January 19, 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Premise==\n''Defending Jacob'' tells the story of a family dealing with the accusation that their 14-year-old son may be a murderer.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |title=Chris Evans To Star In 'Defending Jacob' Apple Limited Series From Mark Bomback & Morten Tyldum |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/chris-evans-defending-jacob-drama-series-novel-apple-morten-tyldum-mark-bomback-1202468564/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= September 20, 2018 |date=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]] as Andy Barber\n* [[Michelle Dockery]] as Laurie Barber\n* [[Jaeden Martell]] as Jacob Barber\n* [[Cherry Jones]] as Joanna Klein\n* [[Pablo Schreiber]] as Neal Logiudice\n* [[Betty Gabriel]] as Paula Duffy\n* [[Sakina Jaffrey]] as Lynn Canavan\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[J. K. Simmons]] as Billy Barber\n* [[Paul Wesley]] as Bobby\n* [[Poorna Jagannathan]] as Dr. Elizabeth Vogel\n* [[Jake Picking]] as Jake\n* [[Nathan Parsons]] as Mike\n* [[Leighton Meester]] as Sara\n* [[Kat Graham]] as Rose\n* [[Daniel Henshall]] as Leonard Patz\n* [[Matt Lanter]] as Jason\n* William Xifaras as Father O\u2019Leary\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |writerT=Teleplay by |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Defending Jacob  \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/defending-jacob/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref> |released=y |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Morten Tyldum]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Mark Bomback]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = Andy Barber ([[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]]) is a respected assistant district attorney in [[Newton, Massachusetts]] who lives a content, suburban life with his wife Laurie ([[Michelle Dockery]]) and their 14-year old son Jacob. Andy is assigned to prosecute the murder of Ben Litkin, a classmate of Jacob's who is found stabbed to death in the park near their middle school. Despite concerns from Attorney General Lynn Canavan ([[Sakina Jaffrey]]) and Andy's colleague and rival Neal Logiudice ([[Pablo Schreiber]]) that Andy's preexisting relationship with parents and students at the school will cause a conflict of interest, he insists on prosecuting the case. Andy and Detective Paula Duffy ([[Betty Gabriel]]) question students at the school, but are unable to discern a motive for the murder. While questioning Jacob privately about Ben, Jacob tells Andy and Laurie that Ben was unlikeable and later expresses frustration to Andy over the exaggerated false sympathy from his classmates over Ben's death. Duffy discovers a possible suspect, Leonard Patz ([[Daniel Henshall]]), a convicted sexual predator, but Andy is advised against bringing him in until they find solid evidence. That night, Andy discovers an online message board memorializing Ben and becomes disturbed after reading a series of comments, including one from Jacob's friend Derek ([[Defending Jacob (miniseries)|Ben Taylor]]), accusing Jacob of murdering Ben. Andy searches Jacob's room and finds a knife fitting the description of the murder weapon hidden in his drawer. \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Everything Is Cool\n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = Andy and Laurie confront Jacob about the knife and message board. Jacob insists he never used the knife and that the comments are meaningless. Andy is nonetheless unsettled and disposes of the knife in a neighbour's trash. The police bring in Leonard Patz for questioning but are unable to implicate him in the murder and he is released. At school, Jacob is approached by a classmate, Sarah ([[Defending Jacob (miniseries)|Jordan Alexa Davis]]), who informs him that Derek has been spreading some disturbing information about Jacob's involvement with Ben. On the way home from school, Jacob sees police outside the house and, panicked, runs away. Meanwhile, Andy is blindsided when he is informed that he has been removed from the case. At the DAs office, Lynn tells Andy that the lone fingerprint they picked up from Ben's body belongs to Jacob and that Jacob has become the prime suspect in the case; Andy is upset when he learns that Neal has been assigned to prosecute in his place. The police obtain a search warrant and Andy and Laurie wait outside their home while it searched. Jacob is eventually found at a playground and is picked up by a police officer. He insists that he is innocent, but reveals that he found Ben's body the morning of his death and didn't tell anyone as he was afraid he would get blamed for it. Andy and Laurie learn that Jacob will be held overnight in jail before his arraignment the following morning. Both Andy and Laurie maintain faith in their son's innocence and return to their ransacked home without their son, while the news of Jacob's arrest spreads throughout town. At a diner, Leonard Patz looks through his photo album, filled with photos of Ben Litkin, before deleting them. \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Poker Faces\n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n<!--{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|1}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|8}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|22}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|29}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}-->\n}}\n\nThe remaining episodes of the first season include, all written by Mark Bomback:{{efn|name=Order|Episodes are currently ordered as they appear on the [[Writers Guild of America West]] website.<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1190756/defending-jacob/ |title=Defending Jacob |website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>}} \n\n* \"After\"\n* \"Damage Control\"\n* \"Ilunga\"\n* \"Visitors\"\n* \"Wishful Thinking\"\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn September 20, 2018, it was announced that [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] had given a straight-to-series order consisting of eight episodes to a television miniseries adaptation of [[William Landay]]'s 2012 novel ''[[Defending Jacob]]''. The series was created by [[Mark Bomback]] who also wrote the series and executive produced alongside [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], [[Morten Tyldum]], Rosalie Swedlin, and [[Adam Shulman]]. Tyldum also directed the series as well. Production companies involved with the series consist of [[Paramount Television]] and [[Anonymous Content]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"SeriesOrder2\">{{cite web |last1=Goldberg |first1=Lesley |title=Chris Evans to Star in Apple Crime Drama 'Defending Jacob' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/chris-evans-star-apple-crime-drama-defending-jacob-1145866 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=September 20, 2018 |language=en |date=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nAlongside the series order announcement, it was confirmed that [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]] had been cast in the series' lead role.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"SeriesOrder2\"/> In March 2019, [[Michelle Dockery]] and [[Jaeden Martell]] joined the cast of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/michelle-dockery-jaeden-martell-chris-evans-apple-defending-jacob-1203168537/ |title=Michelle Dockery, Jaeden Martell Join Chris Evans in Apple Series 'Defending Jacob' |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Joe |last=Otterson |date=March 20, 2019 |accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, [[Cherry Jones]], [[Pablo Schreiber]], [[Betty Gabriel]] and [[Sakina Jaffrey]] joined the cast of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/defending-jacob-cherry-jones-pablo-schreiber-betty-gabriel-sakina-jaffrey-apple-series-1202589226/ |title='Defending Jacob': Cherry Jones, Pablo Schreiber, Betty Gabriel & Sakina Jaffrey Round Out Series Regular Cast Of Apple Series |website=Deadline Hollywood |first=Denise |last=Petski |date=April 5, 2019 |accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> [[J. K. Simmons]] was revealed as part of the cast in a March 2020 trailer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/apple-tv-first-trailer-chris-evans-defending-jacob-1202220114/ |title=\u2018Defending Jacob\u2019 First Trailer: Apple TV+ Unveils Chris Evans\u2019 New Legal Series |publisher=IndieWire |date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming was confirmed to commence in [[Newton, Massachusetts|Newton]], [[Massachusetts]]\u2013\u2013the city in which the novel takes place\u2013\u2013in April 2019. Three locations have been confirmed for filming thus far: Cold Spring Park, the village of [[Newton Highlands, Massachusetts|Newton Highlands]], and the [[Mount Ida College|UMass Amherst Mount Ida Campus]].  Additional filming has begun in [[Belmont, Massachusetts]]. Filming also began in [[Salem, Massachusetts]], on June 15, 2019, as well as at MCI Cedar Junction in [[Walpole, Massachusetts]], on June 17, 2019, and in [[Lowell, Massachusetts]], by the [[UMASS Lowell|UMass Lowell]] [[Tsongas Center|Tsongas Arena]] on June 19, 2019. Filming took place at River's Edge in [[Medford, Massachusetts]], on June 21, 2019. Filming also commenced on June 28, 2019, in [[Worcester, Massachusetts]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lowellsun.com/local/ci_32692189/actor-chris-evans-films-lowell-upcoming-series |website=[[Lowell Sun]] |first=Nicole |last=DeFeudis |title=Actor Chris Evans films in Lowell for upcoming series |date=June 20, 2019 |accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://patch.com/massachusetts/newton/crime-drama-miniseries-be-filmed-newton |title=Newton Picked For Apple TV Series Starring Chris Evans |website=[[Patch Media]] |first=Jenna |last=Fisher |date=March 21, 2019 |accessdate=March 21, 2019}}</ref> and on July 8, 2019, in [[Watertown, Massachusetts]], where the facade of the old Watertown Police Station will appear as the Newton Police Station in the series. Filming took place on July 9, 2019 at the [[Town Diner]] in Watertown. On July 18, 2019, they filmed at C&M Pizza in Leominster, Massachusetts. Neighborhood scenes were filmed in Needham, Massachusetts.\n\n==Reception==\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has an approval rating of 52% based on reviews from 27 critics, with an average rating of 6.09 out of 10. The website's critical consensus is, \"Despite outstanding work from Michelle Dockery and Chris Evans, ''Defending Jacob'' stretches its source material too thin, undermining its own rich tension with too much melodramatic padding.\"<ref>{{cite web |title= Defending Jacob: Miniseries |url= https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/defending_jacob/85309 |website= [[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date= April 24, 2020 }}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the series has a weighted average score of 60 out of 100 based on reviews from 21 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |title= Defending Jacob |url= https://www.metacritic.com/tv/defending-jacob/season-1 |website= [[Metacritic]] |access-date= April 25, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2304589}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|tv/defending_jacob}}\n* {{Metacritic television|defending-jacob}}\n\n{{Apple TV+}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Defending Jacob}}\n[[Category:2020s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Apple TV+ original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Anonymous Content]]\n[[Category:Television series by Paramount Television]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on American novels]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| name                     = Defending Jacob\n| image                    = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Crime drama]]\n| creator                  = [[Mark Bomback]]\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Defending Jacob]]''|[[William Landay]]}}\n| writer                   = Mark Bomback\n| director                 = [[Morten Tyldum]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]]\n* [[Michelle Dockery]]\n* [[Jaeden Martell]]\n* [[Cherry Jones]]\n* [[Pablo Schreiber]]\n* [[Betty Gabriel]]\n* [[Sakina Jaffrey]]\n}}\n| composer                 = [[Atli Orvarsson]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = \n| num_episodes             = 3\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Mark Bomback\n* Chris Evans\n* Morten Tyldum\n* Rosalie Swedlin\n* Adam Shulman\n}}\n| producer                 = \n| cinematography           = [[Jonathan Freeman (cinematographer)|Jonathan Freeman]]\n| editor                   = \n| runtime                  = \n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* Mimir Films\n* Mark Bomback Productions\n* {{nowrap|[[Paramount Television Studios]]}}\n* [[Anonymous Content]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| network                  = [[Apple TV+]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = \n}}\n'''''Defending Jacob''''' is an American [[crime drama]] [[web television]] miniseries, based on the [[Defending Jacob|novel of the same name]] by [[William Landay]], produced by [[Apple TV+]]. The series was created and written by [[Mark Bomback]] and directed by [[Morten Tyldum]]. It stars [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], [[Michelle Dockery]], [[Jaeden Martell]], [[Cherry Jones]], [[Pablo Schreiber]], [[Betty Gabriel]], and [[Sakina Jaffrey]]. It premiered on April 24, 2020.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/apple-tv-plus-amazing-stories-premiere-date-1203472094/ |last=Turchiano |first=Danielle |title=Apple TV Plus Announces Premiere Dates for Steven Spielberg\u2019s \u2018Amazing Stories,\u2019 \u2018Defending Jacob,\u2019 More |date=January 19, 2020 |accessdate=January 19, 2020}}</ref> \n\n==Premise==\n''Defending Jacob'' tells the story of a family dealing with the accusation that their 14-year-old son may be a murderer.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |title=Chris Evans To Star In 'Defending Jacob' Apple Limited Series From Mark Bomback & Morten Tyldum |url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/chris-evans-defending-jacob-drama-series-novel-apple-morten-tyldum-mark-bomback-1202468564/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date= September 20, 2018 |date=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]] as Andy Barber\n* [[Michelle Dockery]] as Laurie Barber\n* [[Jaeden Martell]] as Jacob Barber\n* [[Cherry Jones]] as Joanna Klein\n* [[Pablo Schreiber]] as Neal Logiudice\n* [[Betty Gabriel]] as Paula Duffy\n* [[Sakina Jaffrey]] as Lynn Canavan\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[J. K. Simmons]] as Billy Barber\n* [[Paul Wesley]] as Bobby\n* [[Poorna Jagannathan]] as Dr. Elizabeth Vogel\n* [[Jake Picking]] as Jake\n* [[Nathan Parsons]] as Mike\n* [[Leighton Meester]] as Sara\n* [[Kat Graham]] as Rose\n* [[Daniel Henshall]] as Leonard Patz\n* [[Matt Lanter]] as Jason\n* William Xifaras as Father O\u2019Leary\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table |background=#000000 |overall= |title= |director= |writer= |writerT=Teleplay by |airdate= |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title=Defending Jacob  \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/defending-jacob/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=March 22, 2020}}</ref> |released=y |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Morten Tyldum]]\n |WrittenBy       = [[Mark Bomback]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = Andy Barber ([[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]]) is a respected assistant district attorney in [[Newton, Massachusetts]] who lives a content, suburban life with his wife Laurie ([[Michelle Dockery]]) and their 14-year old son Jacob. Andy is assigned to prosecute the murder of Ben Litkin, a classmate of Jacob's who is found stabbed to death in the park near their middle school. Despite concerns from Attorney General Lynn Canavan ([[Sakina Jaffrey]]) and Andy's colleague and rival Neal Logiudice ([[Pablo Schreiber]]) that Andy's preexisting relationship with parents and students at the school will cause a conflict of interest, he insists on prosecuting the case. Andy and Detective Paula Duffy ([[Betty Gabriel]]) question students at the school, but are unable to discern a motive for the murder. While questioning Jacob privately about Ben, Jacob tells Andy and Laurie that Ben was unlikeable and later expresses frustration to Andy over the exaggerated false sympathy from his classmates over Ben's death. Duffy discovers a possible suspect, Leonard Patz ([[Daniel Henshall]]), a convicted sexual predator, but Andy is advised against bringing him in until they find solid evidence. That night, Andy discovers an online message board memorializing Ben and becomes disturbed after reading a series of comments, including one from Jacob's friend Derek ([[Defending Jacob (miniseries)|Ben Taylor]]), accusing Jacob of murdering Ben. Andy searches Jacob's room and finds a knife fitting the description of the murder weapon hidden in his drawer. \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = Everything Is Cool\n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = Andy and Laurie confront Jacob about the knife and message board. Jacob insists he never used the knife and that the comments are meaningless. Andy is nonetheless unsettled and disposes of the knife in a neighbour's trash. The police bring in Leonard Patz for questioning but are unable to implicate him in the murder and he is released. At school, Jacob is approached by a classmate, Sarah ([[Defending Jacob (miniseries)|Jordan Alexa Davis]]), who informs him that Derek has been spreading some disturbing information about Jacob's involvement with Ben. On the way home from school, Jacob sees police outside the house and, panicked, runs away. Meanwhile, Andy is blindsided when he is informed that he has been removed from the case. At the DAs office, Lynn tells Andy that the lone fingerprint they picked up from Ben's body belongs to Jacob and that Jacob has become the prime suspect in the case; Andy is upset when he learns that Neal has been assigned to prosecute in his place. The police obtain a search warrant and Andy and Laurie wait outside their home while it searched. Jacob is eventually found at a playground and is picked up by a police officer. He insists that he is innocent, but reveals that he found Ben's body the morning of his death and didn't tell anyone as he was afraid he would get blamed for it. Andy and Laurie learn that Jacob will be held overnight in jail before his arraignment the following morning. Both Andy and Laurie maintain faith in their son's innocence and return to their ransacked home without their son, while the news of Jacob's arrest spreads throughout town. At a diner, Leonard Patz looks through his photo album, filled with photos of Ben Litkin, before deleting them. \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title           = Poker Faces\n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|24}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n<!--{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|1}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 5\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|8}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 6\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|15}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 7\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|22}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 8\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Morten Tyldum\n |WrittenBy       = Mark Bomback\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|29}}\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 000\n}}-->\n}}\n\nThe remaining episodes of the first season include, all written by Mark Bomback:{{efn|name=Order|Episodes are currently ordered as they appear on the [[Writers Guild of America West]] website.<ref name=\"WGA\">{{Cite web |url=https://directories.wga.org/project/1190756/defending-jacob/ |title=Defending Jacob |website=[[Writers Guild of America West]] |access-date=March 22, 2020}}</ref>}} \n\n* \"After\"\n* \"Damage Control\"\n* \"Ilunga\"\n* \"Visitors\"\n* \"Wishful Thinking\"\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nOn September 20, 2018, it was announced that [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] had given a straight-to-series order consisting of eight episodes to a television miniseries adaptation of [[William Landay]]'s 2012 novel ''[[Defending Jacob]]''. The series was created by [[Mark Bomback]] who also wrote the series and executive produced alongside [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]], [[Morten Tyldum]], Rosalie Swedlin, and [[Adam Shulman]]. Tyldum also directed the series as well. Production companies involved with the series consist of [[Paramount Television]] and [[Anonymous Content]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"SeriesOrder2\">{{cite web |last1=Goldberg |first1=Lesley |title=Chris Evans to Star in Apple Crime Drama 'Defending Jacob' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/chris-evans-star-apple-crime-drama-defending-jacob-1145866 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=September 20, 2018 |language=en |date=September 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nAlongside the series order announcement, it was confirmed that [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]] had been cast in the series' lead role.<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\"/><ref name=\"SeriesOrder2\"/> In March 2019, [[Michelle Dockery]] and [[Jaeden Martell]] joined the cast of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/michelle-dockery-jaeden-martell-chris-evans-apple-defending-jacob-1203168537/ |title=Michelle Dockery, Jaeden Martell Join Chris Evans in Apple Series 'Defending Jacob' |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Joe |last=Otterson |date=March 20, 2019 |accessdate=March 20, 2019}}</ref> In April 2019, [[Cherry Jones]], [[Pablo Schreiber]], [[Betty Gabriel]] and [[Sakina Jaffrey]] joined the cast of the series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/defending-jacob-cherry-jones-pablo-schreiber-betty-gabriel-sakina-jaffrey-apple-series-1202589226/ |title='Defending Jacob': Cherry Jones, Pablo Schreiber, Betty Gabriel & Sakina Jaffrey Round Out Series Regular Cast Of Apple Series |website=Deadline Hollywood |first=Denise |last=Petski |date=April 5, 2019 |accessdate=April 5, 2019}}</ref> [[J. K. Simmons]] was revealed as part of the cast in a March 2020 trailer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/apple-tv-first-trailer-chris-evans-defending-jacob-1202220114/ |title=\u2018Defending Jacob\u2019 First Trailer: Apple TV+ Unveils Chris Evans\u2019 New Legal Series |publisher=IndieWire |date=March 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nFilming was confirmed to commence in [[Newton, Massachusetts|Newton]], [[Massachusetts]]\u2013\u2013the city in which the novel takes place\u2013\u2013in April 2019. Three locations have been confirmed for filming thus far: Cold Spring Park, the village of [[Newton Highlands, Massachusetts|Newton Highlands]], and the [[Mount Ida College|UMass Amherst Mount Ida Campus]].  Additional filming has begun in [[Belmont, Massachusetts]]. Filming also began in [[Salem, Massachusetts]], on June 15, 2019, as well as at MCI Cedar Junction in [[Walpole, Massachusetts]], on June 17, 2019, and in [[Lowell, Massachusetts]], by the [[UMASS Lowell|UMass Lowell]] [[Tsongas Center|Tsongas Arena]] on June 19, 2019. Filming took place at River's Edge in [[Medford, Massachusetts]], on June 21, 2019. Filming also commenced on June 28, 2019, in [[Worcester, Massachusetts]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lowellsun.com/local/ci_32692189/actor-chris-evans-films-lowell-upcoming-series |website=[[Lowell Sun]] |first=Nicole |last=DeFeudis |title=Actor Chris Evans films in Lowell for upcoming series |date=June 20, 2019 |accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://patch.com/massachusetts/newton/crime-drama-miniseries-be-filmed-newton |title=Newton Picked For Apple TV Series Starring Chris Evans |website=[[Patch Media]] |first=Jenna |last=Fisher |date=March 21, 2019 |accessdate=March 21, 2019}}</ref> and on July 8, 2019, in [[Watertown, Massachusetts]], where the facade of the old Watertown Police Station will appear as the Newton Police Station in the series. Filming took place on July 9, 2019 at the [[Town Diner]] in Watertown. On July 18, 2019, they filmed at C&M Pizza in Leominster, Massachusetts. Neighborhood scenes were filmed in Needham, Massachusetts.\n\n==Reception==\nOn [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the series has an approval rating of 52% based on reviews from 27 critics, with an average rating of 6.09 out of 10. The website's critical consensus is, \"Despite outstanding work from Michelle Dockery and Chris Evans, ''Defending Jacob'' stretches its source material too thin, undermining its own rich tension with too much melodramatic padding.\"<ref>{{cite web |title= Defending Jacob: Miniseries |url= https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/defending_jacob/85309 |website= [[Rotten Tomatoes]] |access-date= April 24, 2020 }}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the series has a weighted average score of 60 out of 100 based on reviews from 21 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |title= Defending Jacob |url= https://www.metacritic.com/tv/defending-jacob/season-1 |website= [[Metacritic]] |access-date= April 25, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2304589}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|tv/defending_jacob}}\n* {{Metacritic television|defending-jacob}}\n\n{{Apple TV+}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Defending Jacob}}\n[[Category:2020s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Apple TV+ original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Anonymous Content]]\n[[Category:Television series by Paramount Television]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on American novels]]\n", "name_user": "98.229.68.193", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defending_Jacob_(miniseries)"}
