e Ages|medieval]] [[Market (place)|market]].]]\n{{Municipalities in Segovia}}\n{{Coord|41|25|N|3|22|W|display=title|region:ES_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://ayllon.info/ Web about Ayll\u00f3n] in [[Barcelona]]'s [[Poble Espanyol]] (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Catalan language|Catalan]], '''[[English language|English]]''', [[French language|French]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Galician language|Galician]] and [[Romanian language|Romanian]]).\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ayllon}}\n[[Category:Municipalities in the Province of Segovia]]\n\n\n{{Segovia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|Lucas V\u00e1zquez de Ayll\u00f3n (1475-1526), Spanish explorer of North America|Lucas V\u00e1zquez de Ayll\u00f3n}}\n{{unreferenced|date=September 2008}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| official_name = Ayll\u00f3n, Spain \n| nickname = \n| image_flag = \n| image_seal =\n| image_map = \n| map_caption = \n| subdivision_type = [[List of sovereign states|Country]] \n| subdivision_name = [[Spain]] \n| subdivision_type1 = [[Autonomous communities of Spain|Autonomous community]] \n| subdivision_name1 = [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]] \n| subdivision_type2 = [[Provinces of Spain|Province]] \n| subdivision_name2 = [[Segovia (province)|Segovia]] \n| subdivision_type3 = [[List of municipalities in Segovia|Municipality]] \n| subdivision_name3 = Ayll\u00f3n \n| leader_title = \n| leader_name = \n| area_magnitude = \n| area_total_km2 = 126 \n| area_land_km2 = \n| area_water_km2 = \n| elevation_m =  1019 \n| population_note = \n| population_as_of = {{Spain metadata Wikidata|population_as_of}}\n| population_footnotes = {{Spain metadata Wikidata|population_footnotes}}\n| population_total = {{Spain metadata Wikidata|population_total}}\n| population_density_km2 = auto \n| timezone = [[Central European Time|CET]] \n| utc_offset = +1 \n| timezone_DST = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] \n| utc_offset_DST = +2 \n| latitude = 41\u00ba 25' N\n| longitude = 003\u00ba 22' W\n| website =  \n| footnotes = \n| }}\n\n'''Ayll\u00f3n''' ({{IPA-es|ai\u032f\u02c8\u028eon}}) is a municipality located in the [[Segovia (province)|province of Segovia]], [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]], Spain. According to the 2007 [[census]] ([[Instituto Nacional de Estad\u00edstica (Spain)|INE]]), the municipality has a population of 1,243 inhabitants.\n\nIn 1411 a treaty, known as the Treaty of Ayll\u00f3n, was signed between [[Portugal]] and [[Crown of Castile|Castile]] ending the wars of the Interregnum.\n\n[[Image:Ayll\u00f3n01-agosto-04.JPG|thumb|left|260px|Plaza mayor with the [[Middle Ages|medieval]] [[Market (place)|market]].]]\n{{Municipalities in Segovia}}\n{{Coord|41|25|N|3|22|W|display=title|region:ES_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://ayllon.info/ Web about Ayll\u00f3n] in [[Barcelona]]'s [[Poble Espanyol]] (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Catalan language|Catalan]], '''[[English language|English]]''', [[French language|French]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Galician language|Galician]] and [[Romanian language|Romanian]]).\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ayllon}}\n[[Category:Municipalities in the Province of Segovia]]\n\n\n{{Segovia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nardog", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingSpanish IPAperdiscussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ayll%C3%B3n"}
